description.narrative: Effective public advocacy on children's rights, by UNICEF Kenya and partners, was increased through strategic communication campaigns and activities. This included partnership events, publications and knowledge products to support advocacy for children's rights; media visits, launches and trainings to improve media coverage of UNICEF's work and children's issues; donor relations support including field visits; engagement of young people, celebrities and influencers; and; creative use of social media and multi-media content for storytelling. As a result, the number of people reached by UNICEF substantially increased, both through traditional media (20 million) and social media engagement (1.3 million). | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
